This folder contains a function a script, and few sample images to perform a semiautomated segmentation of a mass lesion in a mammogram. It is a simplified version of the segmentation algorithm developed in the paper by P Delogu, ME Fantacci, P Kasae, A Retico, Computers in Biology and Medicine 37 (2007) 1479 – 1491. 

The user has to choose interactively a rectangular portion of the mammogram around the lesion, and the algorithm will identify the mass borders and provide the lesion mask.

The function mass_segment.m calls the two custom functions draw_radial_lines.m and max_var_points_interp.m

You can try how mass_segment.m works on the sample images provided here (0016p1_2_1.pgm, 0025p1_4_1.pgm and 0036p1_1_1.pgm). 
Malignant masses are named as xxxx_1.png, whereas benign ones as xxxx_2.png.

The script run_segmentation.m allows you to run mass_segment.m on all *.png files of a directory. It implements also the possibility to repeat the semiautomated segmentation if the result is not satisfactory.
